sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP (PyTorch)
    participant Worker as Worker Pod<br/>Dynamic TCP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Collection
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet<br/>Health Checks

    Note over User,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Training Job Submission
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>Auth: kubeconfig credentials
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>mTLS (API Server cert)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Validation Response<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Job Reconciliation
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch PyTorchJob<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Pods, Services<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created

    Note over Master,Worker: Flow 4: Distributed Training
    Worker->>Master: Training coordination<br/>23456/TCP plaintext
    Master->>Worker: Model sync<br/>Dynamic TCP plaintext
    Note over Master,Worker: Framework-specific protocols<br/>No encryption enforced

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 2: Metrics Collection
    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>No auth
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Operator metrics

    Note over Kubelet,Controller: Flow 3: Health Monitoring
    Kubelet->>Controller: GET /healthz<br/>8081/TCP HTTP<br/>No auth
    Controller-->>Kubelet: OK
    Kubelet->>Controller: GET /readyz<br/>8081/TCP HTTP<br/>No auth
    Controller-->>Kubelet: OK
